<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78bd27fd-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s831cc"><num value="831cc">§ 831cc.</num><heading> Separability</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The sections of this chapter are declared to be separable, and in the event any one or more sections of this chapter be held to be unconstitutional, the same shall not affect the validity of other sections of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78bd27fe-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1933-05-18/ch32/s30">May 18, 1933, ch. 32, § 30</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/48/72">48 Stat. 72</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1935-08-31/ch836/s15">Aug. 31, 1935, ch. 836, § 15</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/49/1081">49 Stat. 1081</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id78bd27ff-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id78bd2800-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id78bd2801-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1935—Act <date date="1935-08-31">Aug. 31, 1935</date>, reenacted provisions of this section without change.</p>
</note>
